  "prompt": "How do I recover a Yahoo hacked email address?",
  "response": "To recover a hacked Yahoo email address, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to Yahoo Account Recovery page\n- Visit account.yahoo.com/forgot\n- Click \"I can't access my account\"\n\n2. Verify your identity\n- Enter your Yahoo email address\n- Choose recovery method (alternative email, phone number, etc.)\n\n3. Account Recovery Options\n- Click \"Send code\" to receive verification\n- Enter the recovery code sent to your alternate contact method\n\n4. Reset your password\n- Create a strong, unique password\n- Use a mix of uppercase/lowercase letters, numbers, and symbols\n\n5. Additional Security Steps\n- Enable two-factor authentication\n- Review recent account activity\n- Check connected devices and sign out of unknown sessions\n- Update recovery contact information\n\n6. If Unable to Recover\n- Contact Yahoo Customer Support directly\n- Provide proof of account ownership\n- Fill out account recovery form on Yahoo help page\n\n7. Preventive Measures\n- Use strong, unique passwords\n- Enable two-factor authentication\n- Be cautious of phishing emails\n- Regularly update account recovery information\n\nIf you continue to experience issues, consider seeking direct assistance from Yahoo support.",
